{"author":{"id":"4cd5c1052fa5d8319cc2cae41adf8d0909d7ec1a59d62a6fe4f0f533b502e203"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1706212262,"nonce":"CFFp4vC7jdkycrCOaa3Ur2MjEkY=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOJl1IZM5x5dvM","github-url":"https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/issues/115#issuecomment-1910889420"},"message":"Given that we have ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/aerospace/ directory dedicated for configuration, maybe we can do all these things there? We can let aerospace.toml be either a regular config or a \"link\" indicating which config should be looked at next. The format of \"link\" will be easy to differentiate from a regular config.\n\nFor example:\n```bash\n-- .config/aerospace\n     |-- aerospace.toml\n     |-- home_mac.toml\n     |-- x86.toml\n     |-- random.toml\n```\nand aerospace.toml:\n```toml\n[[link]]\nfilename = \"home_mac\"\nhostname = \"home_mac\"\n[[link]]\nfilename = \"x86\"\narch = \"x86_64\"\n[[link]]\nfilename = \"random\"\narch = \"arm64\"\nhostname = \"good\"\n```\nwhere we choose the first matched config.","files":null}]}